PARAGRAPH.#text: Moody's Investors Service put Starbucks Corp. SBUX on review for an upgrade, citing in part the coffee giant's improving profits. PARAGRAPH.#text: Kraft Foods Group KRFT said Tuesday that Teri List-Stoll will succeed Timothy McLevish as the company's chief financial officer in the first quarter of 2014. PARAGRAPH.#text: Early trades in shares of Kraft Foods Group Inc. KRFT were canceled after the shares jumped more than 25% within a minute of the market's open. Shares of Kraft Foods rose sharply in the seconds after trading began Wednesday, soaring more than $12 to hit $58.54 in a series of trades well above the opening price of $45.55. Nasdaq OMX Group Inc. NDAQ later disclosed it would cancel all trades in Kraft Foods above $47.82 that were executed between 9:30 a.m. EDT and 9:31 a.m. EDT, calling the trading "clearly erroneous." Nasdaq OMX and Kraft Foods Group representatives didn't immediately respond to requests for comment.
